Modules is very USEFUL because:
1. it can be access by both local and serverscript.
2. the information or function inside it can be access by on (1).
3. can be useful for making huge projects.
4. you can pretty much put it in every container on the ROBLOX STUDIO, depending on how you use it.
5. Module Syntax-- local module = {} - a local variable just simple called module and its a table, so what does this means? this pretty much tells
us that a module script in reality is pretty much a table you can pretty much put inside of the table whatever you want.
6. Module Syntax2-- return module - this line of script will return the line of script full of information that we put
6. Module Syntax3-- the table its the -- local module = {this}        So its like this -- local module = {this is the table}
                                                                                                      
                                                                                          return module
7. Using the Module-- if you want to use it you would need to use a different serverscript and local script, it acts like a toolbox that every script
and local scripts are the USER of the toolbox
8. Using the table-- local module = { part = Instance.new("Part", workspace) } - and the-- return module.
9. The Module USER (ServerScript)-- local moduleUser = require(game.ReplicatedStorage.Shared.Services.Modules.module)
                                    
                                    local part = moduleUser.part
                                    part.Size = Vector3.new(100, 100, 100)
                                    part.Position = Vector3.new(0, 1250, 0)
10. WITHOUT Using The Table-- local module = {}
                              
                              local part = Instance.new("Part", workspace)
                              part.Size = Vector3.new(100, 100, 100)
                              part.Position = Vector3.new(0, 1225, 0)

                              return module
11. Module User THIS IS REALLY SIMPLE only ONE LINE -- local moduleUser = require(game.ReplicatedStorage.Shared.Services.Modules.module) 
